Update:
My current hacky workaround — make hidden WebView, and normal form using Flutter native widgets, then fill and submit the web form using `evaluateJavascript()` like that:
```
_webViewController.evaluateJavascript("""
        document.getElementById("login").value = "${_logInTextFieldController.text}";
        document.getElementById("password").value = "${_passwordTextFieldController.text}";
        document.getElementById("form").submit();
      """);
```
